026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fgs_summer.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fgs_summer.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fgs_summer.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fgs_summer.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fgs_summer.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/fgs_summer.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Future\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhere to watch:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@FutureGamesShow\"\u003eYouTube\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.twitch.tv/futuregamesshow\"\u003eTwitch\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/gamesradarplus/\"\u003eFacebook\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@futuregamesshow\"\u003eTikTok\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhen it starts:\u003c/strong\u003e Saturday, June 7, at 1 p.m. PST/4 p.m. EST/9 p.m. BST\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe \u003cstrong\u003eFuture Games Show Summer Showcase\u003c/strong\u003e promises to highlight “some of the most exciting games on the horizon,” with world premieres, exclusive game demos, developer interviews, and new trailers from more than 40 games. Confirmed to appear are Supermassive Games’ \u003cem\u003eDirective 8020\u003c/em\u003e, Hangar 13’s \u003cem\u003eMafia: The Old Country\u003c/em\u003e , and \u003cem\u003eCrisol: Theater of Idols\u003c/em\u003e from Blumhouse Games. Actors Laura Bailey and Matthew Mercer will host this year’s Future Games Show Summer Showcase.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"xbox-games-showcase-2025\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eXbox Games Showcase 2025\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/2025_FINAL_RGB_DUAL_16x9_TUNEIN-4917eeca9dbbf3f2c985.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1080\" data-pswp-width=\"1920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A graphic for the Xbox Games Showcase and The Outer Worlds 2 Direct\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/2025_FINAL_RGB_DUAL_16x9_TUNEIN-4917eeca9dbbf3f2c985.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/2025_FINAL_RGB_DUAL_16x9_TUNEIN-4917eeca9dbbf3f2c985.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/2025_FINAL_RGB_DUAL_16x9_TUNEIN-4917eeca9dbbf3f2c985.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/2025_FINAL_RGB_DUAL_16x9_TUNEIN-4917eeca9dbbf3f2c985.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/05/2025_FINAL_RGB_DUAL_16x9_TUNEIN-4917eeca9dbbf3f2c985.jpg?quality=90\u0026am